backgroundColor.comment: The background color of the image expressed as a Hexadecimal color specifier
dataValueColor.comment: The color of the text values for major categories expressed as a Hexadecimal color specifier
graphLineDarkColor.comment: The color to use for the right and top borders of the blot graph, expressed as a Hexadecimal color specifier
graphLineLightColor.comment: The color to use for the left and bottom borders of the plot graph, expressed as a Hexadecimal color specifier
hashrateNormalDotFillColor.comment: The color to plot a dot for the hashrate when normal at a point in time expressed as a Hexadecimal color specifier
hashrateNormalDotOutlineColor.comment: The color to make the outline of plotted dots for normal hashrate expressed as a Hexadecimal color specifier
hashrateLowDotFillColor.comment: The color to plot a dot for the hashrate when it below the low threshold at a point in time expressed as a Hexadecimal color specifier
hashrateLowDotOutlineColor.comment: The color to make the outline of plotted dots for low hashrate expressed as a Hexadecimal color specifier
hashrateLowThreshold.comment: The hashrate level for which hashing should be considered low
hashrateZeroDotFillColor.comment: The color to plot a dot for the hashrate when it is zero/unreported at a point in time expressed as a Hexadecimal color specifier
hashrateZeroDotOutlineColor.comment: The color to make the outline of plotted dots for zero/unreported hashrate expressed as a Hexadecimal color specifier
height.comment: The height, in pixels to generate the image.
interval.comment: The amount of time, in seconds, the script should wait before data gathering and image creation again
movingAverageColor.comment: The color to use for the moving average line expressed as a Hexadecimal color specifier
textColor.comment: The color of the text expressed as a Hexadecimal color specifier
useTor.comment: Indicates whether remote calls should use tor socks proxy for privacy.
width.comment: The width, in pixels to generate the image.
